In [ ]:
path = os.getcwd()+"/clean_Montreal_property_listings.xlsx"
data = pd.read_excel(path)
data = data.loc[data.bedrooms < 5]
data['pricem'] = data['price']/1000000

Check the distribution of property prices.

In [ ]:
sns.set(font_scale= 2)
sns.set_style('whitegrid')
plt.figure(figsize= (20,7))
plt.title('Distribution of Property Prices')
sns.distplot(data.pricem, kde = False, color = 'green', hist_kws=dict(alpha=1))
plt.xlabel('Listed Price (in Million Dollars)')
plt.ylabel('Number of Listings')
plt.xticks(np.arange(0.2, 3.0, 0.3))
plt.xlim(0.2, );

Above figure shows that majority of the residential property prices in Montreal lie in a range between 0.2-1.0 million dollars.

Another nice way to visualize the distribution of property prices is using violin plot overlapped with the swarm plot, as shown below.

In [ ]:

In [ ]:
sns.set(font_scale= 2)
sns.set_style('whitegrid')
plt.figure(figsize= (20,7))
sns.boxplot(y = data.pricem, x = data.bedrooms ,color = 'green', boxprops=dict(alpha=1))
plt.grid()
plt.xlabel('Number of Bedrooms')
plt.ylabel('Listed Price \n (in Million Dollars')
plt.title('Distribution of Properties Prices For a Given Number of Bedrooms');

The horizontal line black inside the boxes in above boxplot depicts the median price of the listed properties. From the above figure, we observe that the median price of the property increases with the number of bedrooms a property contains.

Apart from the number of bedrooms, the property prices can also vary within different regions of the city.

order = sorted(data.region.unique().tolist())
sns.barplot(x = data_new.price/1000000, y = data_new.region, palette="husl", hue= data_new.bedrooms, order = order)
plt.grid()
plt.xlabel('Average House Price \n(in Million Dollars)')
plt.ylabel('')
plt.title('Distribution of Listings For a Given Number of Bedrooms');

Check the variation in the listed property prices in different regions of Montreal.

plt.ylabel('')

The exploratory data analysis shows that both the number of bedrooms a property contains, as well as the region where a property is located are important factors in determinig the listed price of the property.
